	<section>
		<h2>Installation</h2>
		<p><strong>Using the npm package?</strong> Run <code>npx rizzo-css init</code> (choose <strong>framework</strong> first, then <strong>add to existing</strong> or <strong>create new project</strong>; create new gives a full clone) or <code>pnpm add rizzo-css</code>. The package includes <code>dist/rizzo.min.css</code>, the CLI (<code>init</code> / <code>add</code> / <code>theme</code>), and scaffolds (<code>vanilla/</code>, <code>astro-app/</code>, <code>svelte-app/</code>) plus optional 24 components. Each scaffold has a README. See the <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/rizzo-css">npm package</a> and project README for CLI details.</p>
		<p>Rizzo CSS is built on Astro. To work on this docs site and reference components (clone the repo):</p>
		<CodeBlock code={`# Clone the project
git clone <repository-url>
cd rizzo-css`} language="bash" />
		<CodeBlock code={`# Install dependencies
pnpm install`} language="nodejs" />
	</section>
	
